{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012KWj2w7Vw2TfRVhGXoEtkP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the bug. Let me create a summary of my findings:\n\n## Bug Analysis Report: Prompts Section Expansion Issue\n\nI've identified the bug in the \"Prompts section\" of the project info page. The issue is in how the expansion arrows handle displaying file contents vs. git commits.\n\n### Location of Buggy Code\n\n**Frontend (UI/JavaScript):**\n- File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n- Lines: 123-139 (the `toggleDiff` function)\n\n**Backend (API handlers):**\n- File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n- Handler 1 - Lines 939-1025: `handleAPIProjectInfo` (loads prompt file history/commits)\n- Handler 2 - Lines 1027-1056: `handleAPIPromptDiff` (fetches the diff content)\n\n### The Bug\n\n**In the JavaScript (`project_detail.html` lines 123-139):**\n\nThe `toggleDiff` function is called when clicking on a commit entry. It fetches the diff between commits using:\n```\n/api/projects/{label}/info/prompt-diff?file={file}&sha={sha}\n```\n\nHowever, there's a **mismatch in what the backend returns vs. what the user expects**:\n\n1. **What the user expects**: When clicking a commit row, they want to see the **file contents** at that commit\n2. **What actually happens**: The backend returns a **git diff** (showing changes between that commit and its parent)\n\n### Root Cause Analysis\n\n**Backend Issue (handler.go lines 1047):**\n```go\ncmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"diff\", sha+\"^..\"+sha, \"--\", file)\n```\n\nThis command shows the **diff of changes introduced in that commit** (the commit and its parent), not the file's full contents at that commit.\n\n**Expected behavior:**\nShould instead use:\n```go\ncmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"show\", sha+\":\"+file)\n```\n\nThis would display the **actual file contents** at that specific commit.\n\n### Files Involved\n\n1. **Frontend Template**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n   - Lines 98-116: Renders the expandable prompt files section with commit history\n   - Lines 123-139: The `toggleDiff()` function that handles clicking on commits\n\n2. **Backend Handler**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n   - Lines 939-1025: `handleAPIProjectInfo()` - Fetches git log for prompt files and returns commit history\n   - Lines 1027-1056: `handleAPIPromptDiff()` - Processes the diff request (this is where the bug is)\n\n### Additional Related Code\n\nThe flow is:\n1. User loads project detail page → calls `loadProjectInfo()` (line 89)\n2. This fetches `/api/projects/{name}/info` → returns commit history for prompts\n3. User clicks on a commit → calls `toggleDiff(this)` (line 123)\n4. This fetches `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=...&sha=...` → **returns git diff instead of file contents**"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae1c2e151824326cf (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 44238\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 23692</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc3b4be9-dd65-41ee-b4f5-ecd52ac62138","uuid":"3fd89fec-8a99-4a5c-a99d-d9c174337e39","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find the code responsible for displaying the \"Prompts section\" in the project info page. The bug is that clicking expansion arrows shows git commits instead of file contents. Look for:\n1. Any UI/TUI code related to \"project info\" or \"project detail\" pages\n2. Code that handles expanding/collapsing prompts sections\n3. Code that reads prompt file contents vs git log/commits\n\nSearch broadly - check cmd/, internal/, and any TUI/UI related code. Look for terms like \"prompts\", \"expand\", \"project info\", \"detail\", \"collapse\", \"arrow\".","agentId":"ae1c2e151824326cf","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the bug. Let me create a summary of my findings:\n\n## Bug Analysis Report: Prompts Section Expansion Issue\n\nI've identified the bug in the \"Prompts section\" of the project info page. The issue is in how the expansion arrows handle displaying file contents vs. git commits.\n\n### Location of Buggy Code\n\n**Frontend (UI/JavaScript):**\n- File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n- Lines: 123-139 (the `toggleDiff` function)\n\n**Backend (API handlers):**\n- File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n- Handler 1 - Lines 939-1025: `handleAPIProjectInfo` (loads prompt file history/commits)\n- Handler 2 - Lines 1027-1056: `handleAPIPromptDiff` (fetches the diff content)\n\n### The Bug\n\n**In the JavaScript (`project_detail.html` lines 123-139):**\n\nThe `toggleDiff` function is called when clicking on a commit entry. It fetches the diff between commits using:\n```\n/api/projects/{label}/info/prompt-diff?file={file}&sha={sha}\n```\n\nHowever, there's a **mismatch in what the backend returns vs. what the user expects**:\n\n1. **What the user expects**: When clicking a commit row, they want to see the **file contents** at that commit\n2. **What actually happens**: The backend returns a **git diff** (showing changes between that commit and its parent)\n\n### Root Cause Analysis\n\n**Backend Issue (handler.go lines 1047):**\n```go\ncmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"diff\", sha+\"^..\"+sha, \"--\", file)\n```\n\nThis command shows the **diff of changes introduced in that commit** (the commit and its parent), not the file's full contents at that commit.\n\n**Expected behavior:**\nShould instead use:\n```go\ncmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"show\", sha+\":\"+file)\n```\n\nThis would display the **actual file contents** at that specific commit.\n\n### Files Involved\n\n1. **Frontend Template**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n   - Lines 98-116: Renders the expandable prompt files section with commit history\n   - Lines 123-139: The `toggleDiff()` function that handles clicking on commits\n\n2. **Backend Handler**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n   - Lines 939-1025: `handleAPIProjectInfo()` - Fetches git log for prompt files and returns commit history\n   - Lines 1027-1056: `handleAPIPromptDiff()` - Processes the diff request (this is where the bug is)\n\n### Additional Related Code\n\nThe flow is:\n1. User loads project detail page → calls `loadProjectInfo()` (line 89)\n2. This fetches `/api/projects/{name}/info` → returns commit history for prompts\n3. User clicks on a commit → calls `toggleDiff(this)` (line 123)\n4. This fetches `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=...&sha=...` → **returns git diff instead of file contents**"}],"totalDurationMs":23692,"totalTokens":44238,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":604,"cache_read_input_tokens":42868,"output_tokens":763,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":604},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
